<br>
Obviously that says a few things: Warriors have problems, the devs know about them for the most part, but they don't have a single imaginative clue how to resolve our issues. <br>
<br>
I think we would get resolution sooner if we absolutly flooded the dev corner or absor's email box (I wish I knew what his email was) with comments about what is broken and that it needs to get fixed. But as for the changes, I am even stumped about what would be easy to change about us to balance the class and make it worthwhile and fun to play again. <br>
<br>
So, we can do one of two things, we can suck it up and take it. This would really not accomplish anything except keeping our frustration bottled up. <br>
<br>
Or we can post to the dev corner and email absor until they finally say &quot;yes we will spend half a year and fix you guys cause you're fuxored!&quot;.<br>
<br>
Either way, things aren't going to change very quickly.<br>
<br>
Aveen Lucenthawk<br>
Myrmidon of 58 Battles<br>
